{"cursor":"1746","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Port |name=East Richford-Glen Sutton Border Crossing |image=Glen\nSutton Border Station.jpg |imagesize=300px |caption=Canadian Border Inspection\nStation at Glen Sutton, Quebec |country=United States; Canada |location='US\nPort:' 357 Glen Sutton Road, Richford, Vermont 05476 'Canadian Port:' 139\nMissisquoi Valley Road, Sutton, Quebec J0E 2K0 |coordinates= |opened=1926\n| blankdetailstitle1 = US Phone blankdetails1 = (802) 848-7746\n| blankdetailstitle2 = Canadian Phone blankdetails2 = (514) 538-3234\n| blankdetailstitle3 = Hours blankdetails3 = Open 24 Hours US / 8 AM to\n| 4PM Canada\n\n| website=http://www.cbp.gov/xp/cgov/toolbox/contacts/ports/vt/0212.xml\n}}\n\nThe 'East Richford-Glen Sutton Border Crossing' connects the towns of Sutton,\nQuebec and Richford, Vermont. During the early 20th century, this scenic road\nwas a major east-west thoroughfare. In 1936, the United States a large border\nstation which is still in use today. By a geographic coincidence, this crossing\nintersects the Canada-United States border at the Missisquoi River. In November\n1927, the bridge at this crossing was one of 45 spans of the Missisquoi\ndestroyed by a major flood. It was soon replaced.\n\nIn 2011, the Canadian government reduced the hours of its border station from\n24/7 to 8:00am to 4:00pm.\n","linknr":96,"url":"East_Richford-Glen_Sutton_Border_Crossing","recorded":1375061426,"links":["/w/index.php?title=East_Richford%E2%80%93Glen_Sutton_Border_Crossing&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=East_Richford%E2%80%93Glen_Sutton_Border_Crossing&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/East_Richford%E2%80%93Glen_Sutton_Border_Crossing","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.D